## Quick Reference — Key GitLab CI/CD Concepts

| Concept | Notes |
|---|---|
| `stages:` | Defines execution order; jobs in same stage run in parallel |
| `needs:` | DAG dependency — job starts as soon as its `needs` complete, ignoring stage order |
| `rules:` | Replaces `only/except`; evaluated top-to-bottom, first match wins |
| `workflow:rules:` | Controls whether the entire pipeline is created |
| `cache:` | Persists files between jobs/pipelines; key-based invalidation |
| `artifacts:` | Passes files between jobs; uploaded to GitLab; has expiry |
| `environment:` | Registers deployments in GitLab's Environments UI; enables rollback |
| `when: manual` | Requires human approval (Play button) before job runs |
| `trigger:` | Triggers a child pipeline or another project's pipeline |
| `parallel:matrix:` | Runs the same job multiple times with different variable sets |
| `extends:` | YAML anchor alternative — inherits job config from a template |
| `!reference` | References specific sections from other jobs (more flexible than `extends`) |
| `include:` | Imports external YAML files (local, remote, template, or other project) |
| `interruptible: true` | Allows a job to be cancelled when a newer pipeline starts |
| `resource_group:` | Prevents concurrent deployments to the same environment |

